modules.description: This module handles serialization and deserialization of BIL (Binary Intermediate Language) components using various formats such as JSON, Protocol Buffers, and Piqi. It provides functions to convert between string representations and BIL structures like `bil`, `stmt`, and `exp`, as well as conversions between Piqi expressions and BIL expressions and variables. Use cases include persisting BIL code to disk, transmitting BIL over a network, or integrating with tools that consume or produce structured data in these formats.

This module provides direct conversions between BAP intermediate representation (IR) elements—such as programs, subroutines, blocks, arguments, phi nodes, and definitions—and their serialized forms in JSON, Protocol Buffers, PIQ, PIB, or XML formats. Each function parses or renders a specific IR component using the specified format, enabling precise loading or exporting of structured BAP data. It is used for persisting, transmitting, or inspecting BAP IR elements in a structured format.
